1. What is Delta Lake?

Delta Lake is a storage layer built on top of a Data Lake that adds reliability and advanced features such as:

ACID Transactions
Schema Enforcement
Time Travel
Version Control
Faster Queries

In simple words:

Delta Lake = Data Lake + Database Features

Database  →  Data Warehouse  →  Data Lake  →  Delta Lake
Small Data     Analytics        Big Data      Big Data + Reliability


2. Database

A database stores structured data in tables.

Examples:

MySQL
PostgreSQL
Oracle


Customers Table

+----+--------+------+
| ID | Name   | City |
+----+--------+------+
| 1  | Rahul  | Hyd  |
| 2  | Priya  | Blr  |
+----+--------+------+


Characteristics

✔ Structured data only
✔ Supports SQL
✔ ACID Transactions
✔ Good for applications

Limitations

✘ Cannot handle huge big data efficiently


3. Data Warehouse

A Data Warehouse collects data from many databases for analysis and reporting.

Examples:

Snowflake
Amazon Redshift
BigQuery

MySQL DB
    \
Oracle DB -----> Data Warehouse -----> Reports
    /
CRM System

Characteristics

✔ Historical data storage
✔ Analytics and BI
✔ Fast SQL queries

Limitations

✘ Expensive
✘ Mainly supports structured data


4. Data Lake

A Data Lake stores all types of data.

Structured
Semi-structured
Unstructured

Examples:

Amazon S3
Azure Data Lake Storage (ADLS)
Diagram

             Data Lake
          ----------------
         /                \
     CSV Files         JSON Files
         \                /
        Images        Log Files


Advantages

✔ Cheap storage
✔ Massive scalability
✔ Supports all data formats

Problems

✘ Duplicate data
✘ Corrupt files
✘ No transactions
✘ Difficult data governance

5. Delta Lake

Delta Lake solves Data Lake problems.

             Delta Lake
          -----------------
          Data Files
               +
          Transaction Log
            (_delta_log)

The _delta_log keeps track of every change made to the data.

